result.execSummary:
All charges against Nija S Darrough in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nija S Darrough is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

8:55 AM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Niki Kane. Defendant Nija S Darrough in court.  Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Nija S Darrough. 

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. 
Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. 
Court advises of right to an attorney. Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  Attorney Gutierrez is appointed. 

The Court notes that attorney Gutierrez filed a Motion to Dismiss.
The Court reviews the motion.
The State objects to hearing the motion as it was not filed 48 hours in advance. 

The Court recesses at 09:02 AM for a ADA to come up to hear the motion.
The Court recalls the matter at 09:18 AM with the following appearances:  Defendant Nija S Darrough in court.  Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Nija S Darrough.  Attorney Melissa Zilavy for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Lesli Boese for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court reviews the motion.
DDA Boese objects to hearing the motion as it was not filed 48 hours in advance. 
The Court takes the objection in abeyance and will hear arguments.
DDA Boese present arguments and requests to deny the Defendant's motion. 
DDA Boese states the offer is withdraw due to the filing of the motion.
Attorney Gutierrez presents arguments and requests to grant the Defendant's motion.
The Court places its findings on the record.
The Court denies the Defense's Motion to Dismiss. 
De Novo rights given.

NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
